&lt;pre&gt;Thanks for breaking this out.

Generally, explainers are meant to foreground the code that users of APIs 
will encounter, and explain how changes in API surface solve the problems 
we are trying to handle. This explainer has WebIDL instead, which isn't how 
we normally do things. I also don't see any considered alternative designs.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Let's dot our &quot;i&quot;s and cross our &quot;t&quot;s here.

