&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://crrev.com/c/6830059/3..10/components/cronet/cronet_proxy_delegate.cc#b95"&gt;https://crrev.com/c/6830059/3..10/components/cronet/cronet_proxy_delegate.cc#b95&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;  a
&gt;&gt;&gt; C++ 17 feature: if statements with initializers
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://abseil.io/tips/165"&gt;https://abseil.io/tips/165&lt;/a&gt;&gt;. It is recommended when a variable is used
&gt;&gt;&gt; within the if statement, but not outside of it.
&gt;&gt;&gt;
